{"descriptions":[{"id":1200,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe perfective past tense is formed by placing after the verb the expressions \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e (assertive), \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་ཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e (intentional egophoric), or \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསོང་\u003c/span\u003e (testimonial).\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn English these forms can be translated by the past or sometimes by the present perfect.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe forms\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003e པ་ཡིན་ \u003c/span\u003e/ \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e are composed of the suffix \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་\u003c/span\u003e followed by the essential copula \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརེད་ \u003c/span\u003eor \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e. The intentional form \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་ཡིན་ \u003c/span\u003emay only be used with volitional verbs in the first person.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIn interrogative sentences that contain no interrogative pronoun (where, who, why, what, etc.), the egophoric form \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་ཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e is replaced by པས་; in sentences where there is an interrogative pronoun, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་ཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e is replaced by \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe auxiliary\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003e པ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e is used in narratives and stories, which is why it is sometimes described as the \u0026ldquo;narrative past.\u0026rdquo; The various forms are as follows:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u0026middot; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eང་ནང་ལ་བསྡད་པ་ཡིན།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;I stayed at home.\u0026rdquo; (egophoric)\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u0026middot; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཉི་མ་ནང་ལ་བསྡད་པ་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Nyima stayed at home.\u0026rdquo; (assertive)\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u0026middot; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཉི་མ་ནང་ལ་བསྡད་སོང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Nyima stayed at home.\u0026rdquo; (testimonial)\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTable: The Perfective Past\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003ctable border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\u003e \u003ctbody\u003e \u003ctr\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eAffirmative\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"132\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eInterrogative\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(without pronouns)\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eInterrogative\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e(with pronouns)\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNegative\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNegative Interrogative\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003c/tr\u003e \u003ctr\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་ཡིན་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"132\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་ཡིན་པས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་\u003c/span\u003e + V **\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་\u003c/span\u003e + V + \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003c/tr\u003e \u003ctr\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསོང་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"132\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསོང་ངས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསོང་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་སོང་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་སོང་ངས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003c/tr\u003e \u003ctr\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"132\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་པས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་\u003c/span\u003e + V + \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e **\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd width=\"113\"\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམ་\u003c/span\u003e + V + \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་པས་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/td\u003e \u003c/tr\u003e \u003c/tbody\u003e \u003c/table\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eNote: The negative forms that are marked in the table with a **, as well as the corresponding interronegative forms, are rarely used, and other forms such as the perfect are usually preferred. The simple past forms may be used to emphasize the subject\u0026rsquo;s refusal to perform the action: \u0026ldquo;I/he didn\u0026rsquo;t go (even though I/he was supposed to).\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཉི་མ་མ་ཕྱིན་པ་རེད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Nyima did not go.\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eང་མ་ཕྱིན།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;I did not go.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:24 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:24 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}